The paper deals with the problem of entity resolution, which is a common issue in databases and information retrieval. The paper focuses on developing new algorithms for collective resolution for answering entity resolution queries at query-time. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
